                       <p>The Weston A. Price Foundation (WAPF), established in 1999, is a not-for-profit organization dedicated to education, research, and activism on health-promoting, traditionally prepared, nutrient-dense, whole foods in the human diet. It has been a pioneer and leading organization in the real food movement, offering annual conferences to help educate the public and practitioners in the US and UK.</p>
                        <p>The Foundation's food recommendations in their annual Shopping Guide and Find Real Food mobile app, are the result of painstaking research to categorize thousands of potential food products into this no-advertisements guide, as thousands of potential food products into this no-advertisements guide, as either "Best," "Good," or "Avoid".</p>
                        <p>These food guidelines are made according to the dietary principles of pioneer researcher, Dr. Weston A.Price, who published the results of his epic 10 year study examining diets and health of people living in hundreds of different cities and 14 countries around the world, in his acclaimed book Nutrition and Physical Degeneration.</p>
                        <p>The Foundation has over 550 chapters worldwide and many thousands of members who are helping spread awareness.</p>
